-- AIG Says Miller Would Step in as Interim CEO for Benmosche
-- B y   H e a t h e r   B u r k e
-- 2010-10-27T21:11:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/aig-says-miller-would-step-in-as-interim-ceo-for-benmosche.html
American International Group Inc.
said Chairman Steve Miller would step in as interim chief
executive officer of AIG for as long as it takes to identify and
select a long-term replacement in the event that Bob Benmosche
would become unwilling or unable to continue to effectively
serve in his current role.  The information was released in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Heather Burke at 
 hburke2@bloomberg.net  